Day of Sun Observed in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 24 (KCNA) -- A meeting, lecture and photo exhibition were sponsored by the Nepal-Korea Friendship Association, the Malta-Korea Friendship Association and the Finland-Korea Society on Apr. 15 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 On display at the venues of the functions were photos showing the revolutionary activities of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il and photos introducing the might of the Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was said at functions that Kim Il Sung founded the Juche idea and the Songun idea based on it and created an excellent model of the cause of independence against imperialism by leading the Korean revolution to victory and he positively supported the anti-imperialist struggles of other countries and made an immortal contribution to accomplishing the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a meeting of communist parties and friendship and solidarity organizations in Nordic countries took place in Sweden on Apr. 13 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.

Anti-U.S. Resistance Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 24 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration in its statement on April 19 called for a vehement anti-U.S. resistance of all the people to realize the desire of those who fought in the April 19 popular uprising.  
 The hearts of the fellow countrymen are still beating with the fighting spirit of the April 19 popular uprising 46 years ago which toppled the dictatorial regime of Syngman Rhee, the chief culprit in causing national division, and opened a new chapter of democracy, the statement said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a serious lesson drawn from the uprising that it is impossible to win democracy and national reunification with south Korea left under the occupation of the U.S. forces, the statement said, and urged all the people to turn out in the fight to force the U.S. troops out of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called upon all the people to turn out in the patriotic movement for independent reunification, for peace against war and for great national unity and put an end to the history of torturous division and fling open a new era of national reunification.

Pro-U.S. Flattery Flailed &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 24 (KCNA) -- The south Korea-U.S. "Alliance Friendship Society" is staging such a disgusting farce as giving Korean-style names to bosses of the local U.S. ruling machines in south Korea including the U.S. ambassador, making sheep's eyes at them.
 Branding the riffraffs of the "society" as despicable fanatics of    pro-U.S. flunkeyism, a Rodong Sinmun analyst Monday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a disgrace and tragedy that there are such traitors within the nation who hit upon the abominable idea, after licking the boots of the aggressors, running the whole gamut of flattery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This treacherous thought must have struck the pro-U.S. elements in their desperate efforts to prolong their days which are numbered, pushed to the fringe by the trend of independent reunification. But their behavior is too shameless.
 Underlying this despicable folly of the fanatics of pro-U.S. flunkeyism is the sinister intention to carry the split of south Korean society to a greater depth and capitalize on it for their return to power. What the traitors of the Grand National Party seek in wirepulling such ultra-right organizations as the "friendship society" to stage the pro-U.S. farce is to divide south Korean society into anti-U.S. and pro-U.S. sections and achieve the tie-up of the conservative forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pro-U.S. treacheries will bring nothing but misfortune and pain of national division and catastrophic disasters of war to the whole nation. Yet, the traitors of the GNP are driving south Korea suffering from tragedies brought by pro-U.S. acts into a deeper abyss of pro-U.S. flunkeyism and gratify their greed for power. Their mental disease of pro-U.S. flunkeyism is obviously incurable before they go to their graves.
 Realities make it crystal clear that independence, progress and dignity are unthinkable in south Korea with the GNP and other groups of pro-U.S. traitors let alone.

KCNA Terms U.S. Assertion about Financial Sanctions Self- Contradictory 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 24 (KCNA) -- The U.S. is now standing more strongly censured by the world public than ever before as the U.S. assertion about financial sanctions against the DPRK proved hypocritical.
 Hill, assistant secretary of State who is head of the U.S. delegation to the six-way talks, addressing the recent Tokyo international seminar on Northeast Asian Security, repeated the assertion that financial sanctions against north Korea are a separate issue from the six-way talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But, after flying into Seoul right after the seminar, he blustered that the U.S. would closely monitor north Korea's financial transaction unless the latter dismantles its nuclear weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hypocritical nature of the U.S. oft-repeated assertion has thus been fully revealed by its self-contradictory statements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world community is deeply concerned about the six-way talks that remain stalled due to the U.S. pressure and sanctions against its dialogue partner and some people even assert that the talks are useless. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is against this backdrop that the U.S. seeks to calm down the worldwide criticism of the deadlocked talks and shift the blame for it on to the DPRK by floating groundless misinformation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent remarks of Hill can be neither an expression of his individual view nor a misstatement. It is no exaggeration to say that they represented an official stand of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard, the world public censured the U.S., saying what Hill uttered is different from its previous stand that financial sanctions are an issue separate from the nuclear issue but related to the U.S. financial interests only. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The inconsistent assertions and statements recently made by U.S. officials over its financial sanctions against the DPRK and its double standards in dealing with the nuclear issue reveal the reactionary nature of the U.S. foreign policy characterized by lies and deception. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Explicitly speaking once again, financial sanctions against the DPRK are an issue directly related to the six-way talks for a solution to the nuclear issue of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nuclear issue surfaced due to the U.S. hostile policy towards the DPRK, a policy aimed at denying its ideology and system and imposing Washington's ideology and system upon it. It is, therefore, the key to its solution for the U.S. to renounce its hostile policy and opt for coexistence with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is hard to expect any solution to the nuclear issue unless the U.S. makes a policy switchover. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. financial sanctions against the DPRK are an obstacle to the resumption of the six-way talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no ground for the U.S. to refuse lifting the sanctions, if it truly hopes for the six-way talks.

DPRK Will Never Allow U.S. to Dare Provoke It 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 24 (KCNA) -- We will consistently react to the U.S. imperialists' hard-line policy with the toughest stance and never allow them to dare provoke the dignified DPRK, declared Kim Yong Chun, member of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and chief of the General Staff of the Korean People's Army, in a report made at the national meeting held on Monday to celebrate the 74th anniversary of the heroic KPA.
 Kim Yong Chun went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have more viciously escalated their sanctions and military pressure upon the DPRK, keeping it on the lists of "outpost of tyranny" and "targets of preemptive attack." They are more zealously plugging the Japanese reactionaries into their operations. They are grossly mistaken if they calculate they can wrest any concession and compromise from the DPRK by whiling away the time through sanctions and pressure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If they ignite a new war despite our repeated warnings, the army and people of the DPRK will mobilize all potentials to wipe out them to the last one so that they may not be able to go back home safe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should face up to the trend of the development of the times towards independence and properly understand the revolutionary will of the army and people of the DPRK, stop acting rashly, immediately discontinue its criminal moves for aggression and war and withdraw its aggressor forces and all means of war from south Korea without delay.

National Meeting Held to Celebrate Anniversary of KPA 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 24 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the April 25 House of Culture here Monday to celebrate the 74th anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army.
 Present there were senior party, army and state officials, including Kim Yong Nam, Pak Pong Ju, Kim Yong Chun, Ri Yong Mu, Choe Thae Bok and Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Yong Dae, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party, Ryu Mi Yong, chairperson of the Central Committee of the Chondoist Chongu Party, and leading officials of military organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Kim Yong Chun, member of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and chief of the General Staff of the KPA, in a report at the meeting said that the KPA has provided a firm military guarantee for the triumphant advance of the revolutionary cause of Juche under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung and the great Party since its founding. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole course of the Korean revolution is a history of the victory of the Songun revolution which was started and has advanced by dint of arms according to the unique idea and line of attaching importance to arms and military affairs laid down by Kim Il Sung, the reporter said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il, who has led the Korean revolution to victory, taking hold on army building as well as party building from long ago, set out the original idea of building the revolutionary armed forces centering on the leader and has successfully embodied it, thus achieving the greatest success in the Juche-based cause of army building.
 The revolutionary trait and the conviction of sure victory of the KPA which has grown to be a core unit, the main force of the Korean revolution thanks to the outstanding Songun idea and Songun leadership of Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il have been fully demonstrated in the fight to defend socialism decisive of the destiny of the country and revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the tasks to be tackled to make a new leap forward in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation with the might of Songun and hasten the independent reunification of the country and the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche, the reporter continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should firmly defend the feats performed by Kim Il Sung in army building and remain loyal to the Songun revolutionary cause led by Kim Jong Il.
 All the servicepersons should consolidate the unity between officers and men based on revolutionary comradeship and successfully combine military and political affairs and become fighters of Ri Su Bok and Kang Ho Yong types in the Songun era who unhesitatingly dedicate their lives to the country, cherishing the staunch spirit of defending socialism and ardent patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to organize all the work on the principle of giving priority to military affairs and direct primary efforts to developing the defence industry as required by the line of economic construction in the Songun era and, at the same time, bolster up the civilian armed forces and consolidate the whole country as an impregnable fortress.
 The reporter declared that the army and people of the DPRK would consistently react to the U.S. imperialists' hard-line policy with the toughest stance and never allow them to dare provoke the dignified DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. imperialists ignite a new war, the army and people of the DPRK will mobilize all potentials to wipe out them to the last one so that they may not be able to go back home safe, he warned, demanding the U.S. face up to the trend of the development of the times towards independence and properly understand the revolutionary will of the army and people of the DPRK, stop acting rashly, immediately discontinue its criminal moves for aggression and war and withdraw its aggressor forces and all means of war from south Korea without delay.

Soldier Family
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 24 (KCNA) -- The word "soldier family" has come into being in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in the Songun era.
 Soldier family means that all its members serve the army, regarding military service as the family tradition.
 There are a lot of such families in the country, which firmly defend the Party, leader, nation and people with arms. Typical of them are the families of Pak Yong Chol and his seven brothers, Om Pok Sun, Ri Chong Song and his four brothers, Ri Jong Un and his five brothers, and Ri Jang Ung and his seven brothers and sister. 
 There are families whose members of three generations are all soldiers. Among them are the family of Ri Chi Son residing in Tongmun-dong No.1, Taedonggang District, Pyongyang and that of Jo Kwan Hwi residing in Kwangsong-dong, Sariwon City, North Hwanghae Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kang Kum Hui working in the Ranam Coal Mining Machine Complex and Han Mi Suk living in Hamhung City, South Hamgyong Province have reared many orphans in their families and tens of them joined the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are beautiful stories about twin and triplet and sister and brother soldiers and couple officers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The origin of the soldier family is the revolutionary family of the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung was the ever-victorious, iron-willed brilliant commander who founded the first revolutionary armed force in the country in his 20s, achieved national liberation and beat back imperialist aggression forces, thus leading the Korean revolution to victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Suk was the woman general of Mt. Paektu who defended the headquarters of the revolution with arms in the anti-Japanese warfare and gave birth to and brought up the future Songun brilliant commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il is the legendary brilliant commander of Songun who has strengthened the Korean People's Army into invincible revolutionary armed forces and is giving full display to the dignity and might of the DPRK with his Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA has been developed to be the army of the Party and the leader, a-match-for-a-hundred strong revolutionary army and covered a proud path replete with heroic struggle and merits over the last 70-odd years. The path is also associated with the ardent patriotism of such soldier families.

Evening Gala of Servicepersons Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 24 (KCNA) -- An evening gala of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces was held at Jonsung Square on Monday to celebrate the 74th anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army.
 Present there were Kim Yong Chun, chief of the KPA General Staff, leading officials of the ministry and KPA servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officers and men of the KPA presented a sea of dances with deep trust in and reverence for President Kim Il Sung, founder of the revolutionary armed forces and leader Kim Jong Il who is opening a new era of building a great prosperous powerful nation with his Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants danced to the tune of songs "Song of KPA ", "Our General Is Best", "Worthwhile Days of Soldiers" and so on.

Joint Press Release on 18th Inter-Korean Ministerial Talks Published
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 24 (KCNA) -- The 18th north-south ministerial talks were held here from April 21 to 24. At the talks both sides issued a joint press release after discussing practical issues arising in settling fundamental issues related to the political, military and economic relations between the north and the south and agreeing on them. 
 At the talks both sides agreed on the following points after appreciating the successes made since the publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and deciding to make positive efforts to put the inter-Korean ties on a higher stage in line with the idea of "By our nation itself": &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
1. The north and the south decided to take practical measures to recognize and respect each other's ideology and system in the basic spirit of the June 15 joint declaration with a view to promoting national reconciliation and confidence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
2. They shared the understanding of the necessity to take practical measures for defusing the military tension and ensuring peace on the Korean Peninsula and agreed to cooperate with each other to this end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
3.  They decided to make sustained efforts for the denuclearization of the peninsula and actively cooperate with each other in the efforts to ensure that the September 19 joint statement is implemented as early as possible to find a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue in line with the common interests and security of the nation.  
4.   They decided to exert efforts for national unity and for the present to ensure that delegations of the authorities of the two sides will take an active part in the grand festival for national reunification to open in the area of the south side on the occasion of the sixth anniversary of the June 15 joint declaration with a view to making this national event meaningful. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
5.  They agreed to have economic cooperation substantially conducive to the prosperity common to the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They decided to take practical measures to actively boost investment and cooperation in areas, types and scope of business for mutual benefit on the basis of firm understanding that the inter-Korean economic cooperation is cooperation between compatriots and an undertaking for prosperity common to the nation.
�@They agreed to hold the 12th meeting of the North-South Committee for Promotion of Economic Cooperation within May for the present to take up the issues of digging up sand at the mouth of the River Rimjin and developing resources common to the nation and discuss the trial operation of trains, the opening to traffic of railways and roads, the construction of the Kaesong Industrial Zone and cooperation in light industry and the development of underground resources, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
6.  They agreed to cooperate with each other in the efforts to substantially settle the issue of the persons whose whereabouts were unknown during the war and in the subsequent period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
7.  They decided to push forward cooperation in various fields including the prevention of natural disasters, health service and the preservation of cultural relics. 
8.  They decided to open the 19th north-south ministerial talks in Pusan from July 11 to 14, 2006.
